<Rate>5<//Rate>< text>
First time visit. This store is phenomenal. Due to covid restrictions we had a little bit of a wait, which I normally wouldn't do, but I'd heard good things about the place from friends. They have an amazing selection (cheese, salami, beer, wine, etc.) despite being a relatively small space. I came for one thing, which unfortunately they didn't have at the moment due to import shortages (not their fault), but I left with a plethora of goodies. I'll definitely be back next time I'm in town.</text>

Holy cow! What an amazing shop! We landed and were crazy hungry. So we did exactly what you shouldn't do and went in hungry. They have a great selection of wines that run across all varieties. Their cheese and meats are equally varied and wonderful. Best of all, the entire staff knows their products backwards and forwards. We ordered two sandwiches to go. Had we known that each one has roughly the dimensions of a skateboard, we probably could've split one. No matter though‚Äîit was delicious.< /review>

<Date>1618503148902< /Date>< text>
What an amazing placed filled with amazing people! We were just in Palm Springs for a week, and we entertained friends at our home multiple times throughout our stay there, and On the Mark was our reliable source for everything but mostly their beautiful charcuterie spreads. They are kind, helpful, knowledgable, and their ingredients are so fresh that we returned 4 of our 7 nights for dinner ingredients, etc. This is exactly what our little city needed, and they were so sweet to accommodate us with a one hour notice for a spread. I can't recommend this place more, and look forward to hosting more of their goodies!< /text>

< Review>
Incredible hole on the wall here. Their catering is incredible but also come in to grab a delicious sandwich and try various very delicious cheeses, spread, mustards etc.

ALSO: TRY THEIR EXOTIC CHOCALATES!! Batch specific, curated chocolates... unbelievable

Their sandwiches use bread baked that am which really compliment the extreme quality ingredients they use to build your sandwich. I had the Wisconsin on fresh baked, moist sour dough with amazing carmelized dark crust... must try, the cheese and meats are out of this world!
As far as catering goes, the presentation is on a board that shows extremely well and of course the foods are on a completely nother level... TRY IT!</Review>

Great place for gifts of a foodie nature. The new store is full of little discoveries. We bought two sandwiches for our flight home. $12.95 for a sandwich and salad or chips. The sandwiches had Grade A ingredients were tasty and in typical American style, huge, not necessarily in size but in filling ingredients. I would say for those who have a light appetite, share a sandwich. Service is great, staff are very helpful. I saw some beautiful charcuterie boards in the fridge. This is just a great place. Well done!</review>

< Text>
I order take out and delivery all the time from here. Order your takeout online and get a free pint of ice cream or 2 liter when you pick up! Also any order placed online for $20 or more is eligible for free garlic cheesy bread, just locate the offer in the specials section of the webpage when doing your online order.  This can also be combined with other online specials.

Only con about this place is the bbq sauce can't be used as a base sauce because it burns too easily. I've found that the garlic white sauce as a base sauce with bbq sauce as an extra sauce compliments it perfectly!</Text>

< Text>
Had been here for evening drinks and snacks which was good. Came back for buffet. Food selection is decent, not much different from any other bay area Indian buffet at this price point. 4 stars because some of the food items were not warm even though we arrived by noon.

Updates from 10/08/2019: changed the rating to 5 star. Visited this place again for evening drinks and family dinner. Great food (I would let pictures do the justice) and enjoyed the service. Will definitely come again for this experience. It does seem like evening menu based food/service is different (much better) than other forms like lunch buffet.< /Text>

<user>107303390996685926363</user><name>Alysia L<//name><Date>1534970816015< /Date><rate>5< /rate>< text>
Came for lunch with a large group, and everyone enjoyed the food at the lunch buffet. Good selection of vegetable dishes and meat plus salads. All the typical dishes: paneer, daal, tandoori chicken and tikka masala. Plus others I don't recall but very good. Fresh naan delivered to the table. They are good at bringing more water since some dishes are spicy. None are incredibly spicy but there's many sauces you can add. They had two desserts: shredded carrot cake and cafe mousse. After Yelp check in it was only around $10 per person before taxes and tip! Great deal and good quality. Not too crowded.

Definitely recommending and coming back!< /text>

We finally made it over to try the new Urban Spice restaurant and really loved every single dish. Some were a little spicey, but we are total babies when it comes to spice. <Text>I'm honestly not the one to give bad reviews and try my best to air on the side of giving positive reviews but this one I just have to say it as it is for the sake of others.

Customer Service/Ambience:
The customer service was good and everyone was nice, the ambience was good as well except it was freezing in the restaurent and even though when I did notify the waiter and the waiter did turn it up a bit (which Haha he hilariously turned it up to 58 degree, I could see it cuz I was sitting right across from the thermostat, I was like whaaat how cold was it before then) but even after that it was still terrible. At one point me we had to stop eating cuz our hands were really cold especially since we were eating with our hands.

Food:
Now the food, I really liked the menu and was really optimistic it would be good. We ordered 3 items 1 appetizer chicken, 1 entre√© chicken and 2 biryanis chicken/goat. The food came out quick and on time.  The moment I took the first bite from each of this dishes it had a strong poultury taste and chicken was undercooked and that really killed my entire experience. And the goat was chewy and not well cooked either. The foods sauce and gravy was good but with the meat being this bad for all 4 dishes  it became a really unpleasent experience, then you add to that the freezing temperature at the restaurent.. just > :(
I even had an stomach ache that night. I'm sorry but I would never be coming back to this restaurant.< /Text>< Pics>

<date>1602006567578<//date><Rate>3</Rate><review>Truckers:

Tough place to deliver and pick up from. The truck entrance is marked with a white sign and is the closest to the intersection. It's a tight turn and there are lots of parked cars and pedestrians so WATCH OUT!

Recieving and shipping open up at 7:00am; don't bother getting there early because there is no room for you to sit and wait. They may recommend that you go down the street to park at the cul-de-sac near the dog park but BE CAREFUL: there are cars that park there and your trailer swing could easily hit one.

<user_id>112123332128881772570<//user_id><Text>Okay, so they told me not to say this, but I really enjoyed the way they had their hands in my mouth.

Jokes aside, I think Pearl Dental is the reason I started going to the dentist regularly again. I hadn't gone for years, but when I needed to get my wisdom teeth out, Pearl was the closest place to my work with positive reviews, so I gave them a try. I was satisfied with how painless the process of scheduling and billing was. They even send me text reminders because I like to forget that I have appointments coming up. The wisdom tooth removal was pretty easy as well. I wanted to "steal" one of my molars to keep because it looked cool, so they offered to clean it before I put it in my pocket lol. Since my first visit there, there have been times when I didn't have dental insurance, but they were willing to work with me with the out-of-pocket costs. Oh, and the staff is super friendly! I like that they have conversations with you even though you can't speak while your mouth is open. Don't like to talk? They can be quiet too. I'm going to keep going to Pearl Dental as long as I live in the area. Oh, and Gloria kindly reminded me to leave this review. I kept telling them that I was going to leave one, but I"m so bad about these things.

< text>
I‚Äôve been here couple of times, but this my first time back on thanksgiving/ 2020.
No parking fee, no entrance fee,
It has a lot of picnic tables, BBQ area, clean bathrooms, staff working here very friendly, and the most perfect place to capture the fall colors, since the air was calm and the sun was out.
It was a little bit crowded, but everybody was wearing masks and they were good with building a distance.
This park provides a lot of different activities ... such as running,hiking, fishing, walking, bicycling, and of course be modeling.
If I stayed a little later, I will be able to enjoy the beautiful fantasy of Christmas lights.</text>

Great place to take the kids, even if you don't go to the lake. The carousel and train are fun and there is a good playground with a model jet to play on. Large outdoor areas for picnics, barbeques and fun.<//Review>

1618952337278<//time>
<Rate>5</Rate>< Review>
This park is so family friendly, it has several benches for picnics. Boat paddling, kayak boats, etc you could rent for 1 hr. The boat paddling is $25 an hour but I would advise to reserve your boat on their website especially if you are trying to go on a weekend!!! Anyways there is also a little train and many ducks walking around the park... overall great place<//Review>

< Text>
Today was a beautiful day out at Vasona Park. Not many people and everyone was being respectable wearing masks. There were some people out walking their dogs. I even saw a cat on a leash. We found a nice area under the shade with a view of the lake and greenery of the grass and trees. Its a nice place to go on long walks and just enjoy the weather.< /Text>

< Review>
This is actually a great park! The similar park to this one is Lake Elizabeth in Fremont which also offers Kayak/Boating in the Lake. Vasona Lake has smaller in size but offers much easier parking. Also the trails are better and easier to access. For South Bay guys, I will prefer Vasona Lake as it is closer to me...< /Review>

<date>1597522435006<//date><rating>4< /rating>< Review>
Too hot to take the boats in the summer. No shadow in the lake. The safe vest makes you even hotter. I do not recommend to go boarding in the summer. Other than that, the lake has beautiful view and lots of parking space, lots of tables for family picnic.</Review>

< review>
Best for one day trip. It's 1hour drive from Oakland. Easy to reach. Several parking lots are available. Picnic tables make our meal time easier.  Park your vehicle based on the location. Lake side pretty crowded. So choose week days. You can walk around the lake. Boating is possible. Good to go with bike. You can see different birds and squirrels. It has washroom in different area of the picnic area.</review>

<Name>Arun Kalyanasundaram<//Name>< user>

< text>
It is well maintained with lots of play structures. It gets crowded quickly because the overall space is small but I think this is one of the well optimized playgrounds I have seen. Kids can keep themselves entertained for couple of hours. The lake is just a minute or two walk and the losgatos creek trail. The sight of the train is fun to watch. Parking at the oak meadow park is better and it's only a five minute walk down to vasona park along the trail. That way kids get a lot of variety.< /text>
</record></dataset><record>
< Review>
Vasona park has natural beauty with lots of tree and greenery. It has a small lake with more than 20 ducks which roam everywhere in the park. The ducks get attracted to you if you give them food or if you carry anything. Trails are best for walking and cycling both. Children's and adults both can cycle and it's fun. The best weather to visit would be with one day when the day is less sunny. Also, there are no entrance fees right now, but remember to maintain social distancing.</Review>

<gmap_id>0x808e35bfb5c787db:0x797f4dd6a28a1c24< /gmap_id><Name>Aaron Bagheri</Name><rating>5</rating>< Review>
I've been going to Vasona Park ever since I was a wee lad.  It's a really nice little park.  There's plenty of grass for picnicking and playing sports, as well as trees for shade.  Various parts of the park have different amenities, such as tables and playgrounds, and there are footpaths connecting all of it.  And of course, there's a really pleasant lake with boat (paddle and kayak) and paddle board rentals!  Wonderful place for a half-day picnic or just for a nice walk.</Review>

<text>Love love love everything about Vasona.  There's something to like for everybody from walking, hiking, biking, roller blading, canoing, kayaking, paddle boating, pic nics, parties, games, concerts, there is litterally something for everyone.  Come pic nic with view of the lake, relax on the lawn, have bbq's with family and friends.  BBQ areas, bathrooms, parking, paved walking trails, fishing, water sports (non motorized) including the sister park Oak Meadow park next door. < text>
Beautiful park with a big lake and lots of trails.
One of the best places for picnics, boating, birthday parties, bbq, biking, etc. Lots of ducks and goose to admire. Their Christmas lights that start from end of November look beautiful!
Closes at sunset so be careful of that! (We got stuck inside and a park ranger had to drive us out. :p )
Cabs can't come in to pick you at an inside parking if the park is closed because they close the gates.< /text>

< Text>
Love this park. My kids even more. It is a very nice clean park and i pretty much there every weekend. It has a nice train ride and carousel. Adults can ride in the train as well. Kids love the park and rides. Also they have onsite bbq hot dogs and I believe burgers. I have never tried them but other seems to enjoy it. Also they have drinks, pop corn and ice creams available as well. It has a nice park with slides, swings, model fire truck and a model jet where kids can climb up have fun. there are lot running tracks, i have seen folks with their bikes there, picnics and birthday parties. I highly recommend this place if you want to have a good time with family.Parking is $6, train and carousel rides are $3 per person. childer under 2 yrs old are free for train and carousel ride.<//Text>

<Rate>5<//Rate>< review>
Love this place. The views are beautiful the trails well marked and the people are usually very nice. Yesterday, when I was walking with my mom we stopped to tell the Ranger that we saw some teenagers tearing down the netting around the playground area. The Ranger was super friendly and kind. I didnt get his name but was very impressed with him! Toward the end of our walk we witnessed a man on bike almost running into a little girl on her bike. The man was extremely rude and began cussing causing the little girl to cry. My mom and I stopped to talk to the little girl and her family. They were very nice and with some kind words we were able to get the girl to stop crying. When biking in a crowded public place remember to reduce speed ( if needed) and be kind. Overall still love Vasona!!!< /review>

< Review>
Things have gotten lot better since my previous review. Boating has resumed, lot more folks use the park and lake. It is a great place for family picnic, even during Covid-19 pandemic. I see people social distancing, wearing mask and enjoying the nature.

My Previous Review
This used be very nice park. My recent visit revealed, things have really changed. Looks like a park in third world country now. Looks like there is no boating in the lake. Construction going on several places. Grass is not maintained. Looks like a disaster. Hope city takes some action and brings it back to its original state. There is still annual fantasy lights during christmas. This is a great place for photo shoot, BBQ and picnic.< /Review>

They've recently renovated the bumpy bike trail on the east side of the lake, and it is smoother and wider than before -- so nice. On weekends, the Wildcat steam locomotive might be running, providing a bit of nostalgia, as well as a quick train ride for the under-5 set (and their parents).<//review>

< Text>
This park used to be the Jewel of the area. Now, it is in a sad state of neglect. The grass has died and weeds are taking over. The ground is not absorbing the water, so, there is standing water near the play ground. (Breeding ground for mosquitoes, this time of year) The geese have taken over in many areas and their droppings are all over the playground; in the sand and walkways, too. To top it off, there is no shade in many areas of the park, and the surrounding areas; where is the heat prevention? (Need more over hangs, where the benches are, and the seated kid rides; the metal is hot!. Water fountains, for cooling stations. Etc) I loved coming to this park as a kid and young adult; now though, I was embarrassed to have brought my friend and his 3 year old. The poor guy was overheating and couldn't ride the swings, or the metal turtle/duck, because they were hot to the touch.
Maybe partner with Netflix, or surrounding companies, to get some volunteers to help out the staff, to return the park to it's once beautiful state?< /Text>
</record>
</dataset><record>
< userid>

<Date>1591487530921< /Date>< rating>
5</rating>
< Review>
Great park but on the trails people are not taking social seriously. If you hang out on the grass you'll be fine.95% stay off the grass.

Oh do Not fly your airplane or drone. It is not allowed, park rules. I flew my drone 2 days in a row. Second day a ranger sped over in her truck and yelled on her truck speaker "Hey you put that away in your vehicle NOW...."!

Not a great experience I had no clue there are no signs to let you know its not allowed. I did find the park rules on their Vasona's website.

I understand everyone including the rangers are frustrated with the virus.

She could have handled me with some politeness. Other people were very upset the way she yelled at me. I'm 47 yrs old and I was with my children and spouse. Although I was playing with my drone. I'm far from being a child. Kindness goes a very long way especially during all our frustrations.

My family continue to enjoy the park its well manicured and the restrooms are well cleaned.

Thanks Vansona Park Team üëç</Review>

< text>
Still a nice place to go for a walk, and the playground is still open, but large areas of the park are closed off for repairs, meaning much of the park, including restrooms, are inaccessible. Orange net fencing everywhere. There are 2 portapotties at the top of the hill next to YSI, which at least appear to be serviced every 3 days, with a place to wash your hands available.

‚ö†Ô∏è A word of caution: I was somewhat surprised to encounter a coyote running around in broad daylight near the Youth Sciences Institute. It was not afraid of me either! Dog-walkers: please be careful and keep your dogs on leash, especially small dogs.</text>

< userid>
110084612765324174402< /userid>
< name>
William Schwartz</name>
< time>
1534205230318</time>
<Rating>5<//Rating>< Text>
Vasona park and lake is one of the best managed public spaces in the bay. Besides the many trails that intersect and connect Vasona lake to bay area bike and pedestrian trails they offer boating, bodyboards,  paddle and sail boats. There are many spaces all with full bbq facilities, playgrounds, bridge, hiking ,fishing and summer  concerts. There is even an ice cream truck on the weekends. The far end of the park has a real scaled down train for people to ride. You cant swim in the lake but with the many water activities there are plenty of fun options. The cost is reasonable per hour for rentals or just relax on a grassy hill. Vasona park is free to walk in. Parking on weekends can be difficult so get there early. The restrooms are clean and well equipt.  Spaces for BBQ need to be reserved in advance on busy days. As well you are only blocks from historic downtown Los Gatos if you crave some great restaurants. Make a weekend of it at Vasona Park! I highly recommend.< /Text>

<time>1596153934758<//time><Resp>None</Resp><gmap_id>0x808e35bfb5c787db:0x797f4dd6a28a1c24<//gmap_id><userid>107069339132307105014< /userid>< name>
Christopher Schoppet-Panzarini< /name>
< Review>
Need to get out? Covid Quarantine Depression getting you down? I found the perfect place for you to escape to and odds are, if you're looking at this, it's in your own backyard.

Spacious and green fields, plenty of room to social distance from others. Water sports available ($18 for single or a paddle board, $23 an hour for the peddle boats) on the quaint, calm, blue lake. Honestly, it is beautiful! Plenty of trails to walk, bike, hike, etc around the lake as well.

There's a fair number of geese that will honk for food if you are having a picnic and they leave landmines here and there but hey, they're still avoidable and lay down a blanket on the grass and you're fine!

While there are tables still available, for single household usage, the group areas are off limits at this time. Masks are encouraged but again there is so much space that you could isolate yourself somewhere and take yours off for a bit if you need the freedom of being maskless outdoors.

Another "perk" during COVID is parking was free. Not sure if that's for always but it was today! That was really nice. With plenty of good restaurants doing takeout in nearby Los Gatos or Campbell, like Thai Spice or Back A Yard or, if you want to get fancy The Bywater (which you can then eat by the water... At the lake... In the park), it's easier than ever to enjoy a quick picnic in a scenic locale away from your home for a bit and off screens for once.

Enjoy!< /Review>

One of the best, family friendly parks in the South Bay. They have nicely spread out picnic tables with grills, paddle boats, kayaks, and rowboats for rent during summer, and a miniature steam engine that takes trips around a section of the park. The best thing about Vasona is it‚Äôs layout. No matter how busy the park, you can almost always find a comfortable section for yourself. If you like jogging, the park connects to the Los Gatos Creek trail near the dam.<//review>

<GmapID>0x808e35bfb5c787db:0x797f4dd6a28a1c24< /GmapID><time>1560069173375<//time><rate>5<//rate><Text>This park has everything you need! Lake, BBQ stations, peddle boat, Kayak,  train, carousel, playground, and restrooms. Through the main entrance, you will pay $6 for parking. If you have a disabe plate, parking is free. The road split off to different sections with plenty of tables.  Some BBQ pit and tables are reserved so be on the lookout for that.  Train ride is about 10 minutes around the main area with $3 per adult. Children under 3 is free. On summer and weather permits, they sell hot dogs and burgers by the railroad station. On weekends, the park fills up quickly so arrive early if you want a picnic table with lake view.<//Text></record>

< text>
Open grassy fields with good supply of picnic tables. Favored by families with young children as they also offer a small train ride plus merry-go-round. We came here by hiking at nearby trails, which I'd highly recommend. Connects up with San Jose to the north, Los Gatos and down to the reservoir to the south. Excellent trails. This park offers the restroom facilities useful on the hike.<//text>

< Review>
I love this park. It's a gem of nature tucked away in the city. Tons of green space, walking and biking trails all surrounding a beautiful lake. I come here weekly with my 2 year old and dog. They have two very nice children's play areas, the park is clean and well kept and it's such a large area you really feel like you're escaping the city. They do charge $6 for parking but it is so worth it. One of the best parks I've been to in the bay area.<//Review>

<Review>Great local park! plenty of open space, picnic tables and playgrounds. Paved walking/biking paths in the park, good for a nice walk or jog. The paths are part of the larger bike path system, so you can either stay in the park, or just pass through as you head further north or south, on a longer ride. On the other side of the park there is a very popular train and carousel ride and a gazebo where they have performances during the summer.< /Review>< response>
None</response>

< Text>
Beautiful park in Los Gatos! Parking is not free, but  I think it is worth it. There is lots of room to walk or bike or run. Lots of green areas for picnics, some picnic tables here and there too.

There is a nice reservoir in the center of the park. There is also a very cool kids railroad running across the whole park. For Xmas the park also puts together a light show.

This is also a dog friendly park, so you can walk with your pooch anywhere you feel like.

Lovely park!< /Text>

Good place to take a walk. There is a small train that kids can ride on. A fee is required to ride. There are some picnic tables. The group picnic areas requires fees. Its a great park and is spread widely. It has multiple bbq spots and open fields. We went there for our team event and I really enjoyed there. They also have boating options but we didn't do that. We did bbq and played games in open fields. There is a parking fee of $6 for full day. Lots of options for kids play area. During Christmas they also have great lighting throughout the park. Definitely a great place to spend your day and just relax. Lots of restaurants option nearby as its located near downtown Los Gatos.<//Text>

The plane. It's been there since before my time.  All kids (big and small)still love it. The park also has one of the last "tall" playgrounds left in our overly zealous safety conscious society (plus a couple other scattered playgrounds on the acerage of park). < review>
This park is great in its diversity.  There are playgrounds, excellent biking and rollerblading paths, picnic areas and a pretty man-made lake.   There is a lot of parking although it does get busy on weekends.   This is an especially nice park for families.   It connects with the Los Gatos trail which extends where you can get on bikes.   The only thing it is missing are enough wild areas and native habitat.  You need to go further up into the Santa Cruz mountains if you are looking for that.<//review>

< review>
Great park. Well maintained, many different pieces of apparatus to have fun on...from children safe firetrucks and fighter jets (mixed amungst normal jungle gyms), baseball fields, soccer fields, to an actual steam train that offers rides and a vintage carousel...all connected by a large network of walking trails. There are many sporting groups that meet in this park as well. I've come here as a child, adolecent, and now adult. Oh, Christmas light drive through attraction during the holidays and there is a theater company that offers shows as well. Really a great park.< /review>

<userid>105233024128207195596</userid><username>Tracy Avent-Costanza</username>< date>
1501262195273< /date>
< Rate>
4</Rate>
<review>Definitely one of the better parks within silicon valley, operated by Santa Clara County, on the north end of Los Gatos near the border of Campbell, also bordering CA-17 freeway. The park is surprisingly quiet for being that close to a major freeway. Generally it is $6 for parking/entry fee per vehicle unless you have a pass. Facilities include extensive picnic grounds (some pre-reserved for group events, the rest first-come-first served). There is a lake with paddle boats, canoes and paddle-boards rental, and the county park is adjacent to a city park where there is a rideable scale-model train whose track goes thru part of both parks.

Vasona also has fairly extensive walking and bike trails, and lies within the larger Los Gatos creek trail, so traffic on foot and on bikes, goes thru Vasona park, between the endpoints of Downtown Los Gatos and the Willow Glen neighborhood of South San Jose.

There are also regular music concerts on saturday afternoons during the late spring and summer, near the boat house.</review>< pictures>
None<//pictures>
